    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-22T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-22T06:30:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2–2252:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 194<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia (<persName type="from"
                            >Cochran</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-22T19:00:00+07:30"
                            >February 22, 1952—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1253. Have just recd <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 923.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d194fn1">
                        <p>Transmitted by the Department of State at 1 a.m. on Feb. 22. It reads as
                            follows:</p>
                        <p>“We note Subardjo’s reasons prefer <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss>
                            Sec 511 (a) to 511 (b) (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 1227 Feb
                            19), and we are keenly aware prime importance 511 (a) to totality of US
                            policy toward <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>.</p>
                        <p>“In view Subardjo resignation, however, and in view great interest being
                            shown here in Dept, <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> and press, we
                            desire that <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt shld have ample
                            opportunity understand that it is possible for Govt to give 511 (b)
                            assurances, as stated Depts A110 Nov 23 or along lines Burmese formula
                                <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 823 Feb 4 [not printed].
                            We are concerned lest in present superheated atmosphere 511 (b) be lost
                            through over-identification with 511 (a).” (756D.5 <gloss
                                target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2–1952)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>Invite Dept’s attention to <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtels</gloss> 1249 and
                        1250<note n="2" xml:id="d194fn2">
                        <ref target="#d192">Document 192</ref> and <ref target="#d193">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>, respectively.</note> giving facts with respect maneuvering by
                    Sukiman and Emb recommendations. Cld not believe that in light thereof, Dept wld
                    risk such humiliation as wld inevitably result from efforts to carry out <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 923 with moribund govt and with only
                    slight possibility Sukiman cabinet cld command sufficient support to conclude
                    any sort <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> agreement with US. Request
                    therefore reconsideration instructions <pb facs="0295" n="275" xml:id="pg_275"/>
                    which wld have gravest consequences on future course US-<gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> relations.</p>
                <p>Cabinet meeting scheduled for evening 22d postponed until forenoon 23d.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
